IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. mfcc.
AUTHOR. Simon Mikkelsen.
* This program is a delightful journey through the world of COBOL,
* designed to bring joy and learning to all who read it.
* It processes input data in a whimsical and enchanting manner.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO RANDOM-FILE.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-LOTR-VARIABLE PIC X(50).
01  WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR1 PIC 9(5).
01  WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR2 PIC 9(5).
01  WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR3 PIC 9(5).
01  WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR4 PIC 9(5).
01  WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR5 PIC 9(5).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE
    PERFORM READ-INPUT-FILE
    PERFORM PROCESS-DATA
    PERFORM CLOSE-FILE
    STOP RUN.

READ-INPUT-FILE.
    READ INPUT-FILE INTO WS-LOTR-VARIABLE
     AT END
         DISPLAY "End of file reached."
     NOT AT END
         DISPLAY "Reading data: " WS-LOTR-VARIABLE
         PERFORM READ-INPUT-FILE
    END-READ.

PROCESS-DATA.
    * This section is where the magic happens.
    * We process the data with love and care.
    MOVE WS-LOTR-VARIABLE TO WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR1
    MOVE WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR1 TO WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR2
    MOVE WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR2 TO WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR3
    MOVE WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR3 TO WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR4
    MOVE WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR4 TO WS-UNNECESSARY-VAR5
    DISPLAY "Processing complete."

CLOSE-FILE.
    * Closing the file with a gentle touch.
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE
    DISPLAY "File closed gracefully."

